        },
        {
          "message": "Fix ActiveJob retry logic (#1415)\n\nIf a `rescue_from` block catches an execption from a job, that job will\nnot be retried.\n\nThis commit switches the error handling into an `around_perform` block,\nwhich, according to my experiments, does actually result in the\n`retry_on` logic being applied.",
